summary:
The Security Council, 
Noting with concern the tense situation in the Middle East, 
Having considered the report of the Secretary-General on UNDOF of 13 June 2011, 
Expressing grave concern at recent events that jeopardized the ceasefire, 

1. Calls for immediate implementation of resolution 338 (1973); 
2. Calls on parties to cooperate with UNDOF and ensure security and access for UN personnel; 
3. Recalls parties' obligation to respect the 1974 Disengagement of Forces Agreement and calls for maximum restraint; 
4. Welcomes UNDOF's efforts to implement zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse; 
5. Renews UNDOF's mandate for six months, until 31 December 2011; 
6. Requests the Secretary-General to submit a report on developments and measures to implement resolution 338 (1973).
